<br>
Generally a mix works best, of course. For an average raid, 2 strong tanks, 5-6 melee damage dealers, 2 clerics, 2 chanters and a bunch of nukers (preferably wizards) works great. If you got it down right and have a very strong tank, you can do it with a single cleric and chanter as noone but the MA should get hurt. But that's a bit risky. The key, as kiti mentioned, is to make sure VS can't use your lower level tanks as HP batteries. Agro management is thus very important.<br>
<br>
Once you have the tank/chanter/cleric, the most important people for a VS raid are really the damage dealers. Especially wizards and rogues, with monks and rangers coming in after that. His lifetap really makes him a special mob, in that you can't compensate for low damage output by having more healing power. You either outdamage the lifetap proc by a significant amount, or you lose. If you don't do enough damage, it doesn't matter at all whether you have enough healers to keep the MA standing for 2 hours - you'll still lose.<br>
<br>
VS is a fairly low HP mob, though his lifetap makes him seem much more formidable. This is why fast damage dealers really shine. If you do damage fast enough, as wizards and rogues excel at, VS is a real pushover. If you have a raid that's losing, try adding another wizard or rogue and see how huge a difference it makes. 16.000hps is what VS has, if memory serves, and even a small group of the fast damage dealing classes can bring this down VERY fast. Often when you lose, it is because you are just barely outdamaging the lifetap, and therefore adding even a single wizard to the raid can turn the tables to make it look easy. <p>Ulaian Moonleaf <BR>
-Warder <BR>
